Body: 应届毕业生在毕业前都遇到了难以获得面试的境遇，投递几百份申请都很难获得面试机会，从而自信心受到了很大打击，对于求职状态造成了很大的影响。那么有哪些原因View this email in your browser 关注北美市场，聚焦数据、软件类求职，60秒解析一个求职问题，每周追踪岗位发布数量，助力求职成功！60秒答疑：应届毕业生为何很难拿到面试机会？应届毕业生在毕业前都遇到了难以获得面试的境遇，投递几百份申请都很难获得面试机会，从而自信心受到了很大打击，对于求职状态造成了很大的影响。那么有哪些原因可能会影响到应届毕业生的求职过程呢？1）缺乏经验：应届毕业生可能没有太多工作经验或相关技能，这会使他们更难在拥挤的就业市场中脱颖而出。2）资源有限：新毕业生可能没有庞大的专业网络，这会使他们更难了解工作机会和获得推荐。3）时间安排：一些岗位要求的到岗时间比较近，没有办法长时间等待毕业时间。所以一些公司会要等到他们毕业时间后才考虑雇用新毕业生。4）严峻的就业市场：在特殊的市场情况下，在某些领域可供应届毕业生使用的工作机会可能更少，这可能会增加面试的难度。比如裁员压力下，会压缩应届岗和实习岗位的机会。5）准备不足：新毕业生可能没有为求职过程做好充分准备，包括制作一份强有力的简历和求职信、练习面试技巧以及研究潜在雇主。新毕业生如果希望提升自己的求职效率，可以考虑采取下面几个步骤来增加获得更多面试的机会：1）拓展资源网络：参加招聘会，加入特定行业的专业组织，并与你学校的校友联系。 网络可以帮助您了解工作机会并获得推荐。2）提前并增加申请数量：尽快开始申请工作并持续申请，即使您之前的申请没有收到回复。 同时增加前期岗位筛选，提高有效岗位的申请数量，获得面试的机会就越大。3）考虑实习或志愿服务：即使您在毕业后无法立即找到一份全职工作，实习或志愿者机会也可以帮助您获得宝贵的经验并在您的行业中建立人脉。4）利用专业求职服务：许多学校和机构都提供职业服务来帮助毕业生找工作。 利用这些资源和服务支持，来对接更多岗位，获得针对性的面试辅导，提高面试效率和成功率。通过采取这些步骤，新毕业生可以提高获得更多面试和拿下offer的机会。AI聘 - 数据类岗位每周岗位发布数据追踪我们来看一下进入2023年3月第3周，AI聘团队对于北美数据类岗位的每日发布情况的追踪数据：* Data Analyst 数据分析师周中平均每日发布岗位数量达到14457，比前一周日均减少了2093个岗位；降幅12.65%；* Business Analyst 商业分析师达到12532，比前一周日均减少了3773个岗位；降幅23.14%；* Product Analyst 产品分析师达到2145，比前一周日均减少了387个岗位；降幅15.27%；* Marketing Analyst营销分析师达到3114，比前一周日均减少了29个岗位；降幅0.93%；* Data Scientist 数据科学家达到11198，比前一周日均减少了387个岗位；降幅2.49%；过去一周，数据类岗位开放数量继续走低，其中商业分析师数量更是出现了超过20%的降幅，数据分析师降幅也超过了10%，数据科学家基本保持平稳。在受到外部市场环境的负面消息影响下，目前的求职市场比较严峻，岗位资源收缩，增加了获得面试的难度，也提升了面试竞争。求职者一定要做好更加全面的准备。AI聘 - Subject: IMPORTANT: Your I-20 is Due to Expire Soon
Body: # IMPORTANT: Your I-20 is Due to Expire SoonDear Chengyan Ji, **Please do not reply to this email.** It has been automatically generated based on your F-1 program end date. Please disregard this notice if you will begin a new graduate program at UIUC or have applied for Optional Practical Training based on completion of your degree. Our records indicate that your I-20 will be expiring within 60 days, since your Program End Date is May 13, 2023. Please check your most recent I-20 to confirm this is the case.See Item 1 below for instructions on extending your I-20 if you will not finish your degree by the program end date on your I-20. See Item 2 for important reminders if you will finish your degree by the I-20 program end date.1) How to extend your I-20 if you need additional time to finish your degree program:* Submit an **[Extension for F-1 e-form on in F-1 Student Services**.* This e-form must be approved by ISSS prior to the program end date of your I-20; once your I-20 expires we cannot extend it.* Please allow ISSS at least one week to process your request once submitted.* If you are employed on campus you must take your new I-20, passport and I-94 to your employing department to extend your Form I-9, showing your continued eligibility to work on campus.2) Reminders if you will finish your degree program on or before the program end date of your I-20:* If you wish to apply for Optional Practical Training (OPT) to take a job related to your field and level of study, there are strict deadlines. Please refer to these [OPT * Your completed application is due at the US Citizenship and Immigration Services department prior to the end of your grace period (60 days after the end date of your program), so visit ISSS well in advance of that date.* If you will transfer to another school you may request that ISSS transfer your SEVIS record. Please fill out the [Transfer Out e-from on Apply prior to the end of your grace period (60 days after end date of your program.) For more detailed information visit the ISSS office.* If you are changing educational level from master's to PhD, please fill out the **[Change of Graduate Program e-form on iStart in F-1 Student * If you are changing educational level from bachelor's to master's, apply for a new I-20 from the Graduate College.* If you are exiting the United States and not returning, you are required to exit within 60 days from your program end date.We know that this is a busy time of the year for you, and we appreciate your attention to this important matter.Regards, ISSS staffInternational Student and Scholar Services 432 Turner Student Services Building 610 E. John Street Champaign, IL 61820 (217) 333-1303 - phone (217) 244-0530 - fax isss@illinois.edu | [Take || [SEVIS Transfer Out || [Take | html

Body: Join us at the zoo April 15-16View this email in your browser TICKETS | MEMBERSHIP | DONATE ** INTRODUCING... SPRING SPECTACULAR!------------------------------------------------------------Come see the Zoo in Bloom April 15-16!Come celebrate all things spring at our inaugural event—Spring Spectacular!During Spring Spectacular weekend all the fun is included as part of your admission! In addition to a zoo visit, enjoy family-friendly activities, live music, games and engaging educational opportunities for guests of all ages.Even our animals are getting in on the springtime festivities! Don’t miss a series of special animal enrichments happening throughout the day all around zoo. Here are just a few of our furry and feathered friends who will enjoy special springtime treats…* Red Panda* Maned Wolf* Tigers* Lynx* Penguins* ... and so many more!In addition to animal enrichment opportunities, there will also be special animal keeper talks and docent carts, arts and crafts on the meadow, expert gardener and horticulturist talks and demonstrations, scavenger hunts and more.Plan your trip now and help us celebrate the season of spring!Purchase your zoo tickets Learn about the importance of native planting and the small, but impactful things that you can do in your own yard to protect pollinators!============================================================OUR MISSIONTo save wildlife and inspire everyone to make conservation a priority in their lives.Our mailing address is:5500 Phinney Ave. N., Seattle WA 98103Set your preference** Manage your email preferences** Unsubscribe from all zoo emails** Privacy Policy To ensure you continue receiving our emails, please add us to your address book or safe list. html

Subject: Computer Science@Illinois Graduate Admissions Decision
Body: Dear Mr. Ji:Your application for graduate study for the Fall 2023 Master of Computer Science (MCS) program in the Department of Computer Science at the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign has been carefully considered by our Graduate Admissions Committee. We regret to inform you that the committee is not recommending you for admission to graduate program. Due to space limitations and a number of exceptional applicants, we are unfortunately unable to recommend many well-qualified students for the program. Therefore, we hope that this decision will not discourage you from pursuing your future academic and career goals.Please note that the department policy is not to communicate the individual reasons for its decision. If you have any questions, please contact the department at admissions@CS.illinois.edu.We appreciate your interest in our program and all of your efforts in preparing an application. Together with the rest of the department, we sincerely wish you the best of luck in your future endeavors.Sincerely,Dr. Robin Kravets, ProfessorDirector of Graduate ProgramsDr. Paul Fischer, ProfessorChair of Graduate Admissions

Subject: =?utf-8?Q?=E9=A1=BA=E5=88=A9=E6=8B=BF=E4=B8=8B=E9=9D=A2=E8=AF=95=EF=BC=8C=E4=BD=A0=E9=9C=80=E6=80=8E=E4=B9=88=E5=81=9A=EF=BC=9F=2F=E5=88=9D=E5=88=9B=E4=BC=81=E4=B8=9A=E8=A3=81=E5=91=98=E5=87=8F=E5=B0=91=EF=BC=8C=E4=BD=86=E7=94=9F=E5=AD=98=E6=8C=91=E6=88=98=E4=BB=8D=E6=9C=AA=E8=A7=A3=E9=99=A4?=
Body: 在面试中展示你在面对客户时的沟通技巧、自信和专业精神，做好充分准备，能给你的面试官留下深刻印象。View this email in your browser 顺利拿下面试，你需要怎么做？ 面试官有很多方法可以测试你是否适合他们的工作。在面试中展示你在面对客户时的沟通技巧、自信和专业精神，做好充分准备，能给你的面试官留下深刻印象。在下文中，我们将讨论如何在面试中表现出色，帮助你增加获得工作的机会。如何准备面试陈述？ 以下是你需要采取的步骤，以提高你在面试中的机会。1）未雨绸缪——在面试之前研究公司和职位 在面试日到来之前，研究一下你所申请的公司和职位。这样做将帮助你确定要为你的演示文稿创建的推介类型。以下是你在研究过程中应该向面试官提出的基本问题：* 公司的主要领域是什么？（了解公司的工作领域将有助于你根据公司的需求调整演示内容）* 面试一般持续多长时间？（确定时间将帮助你决定在演示文稿中添加或删除哪些内容）* 面试官是谁？（借此弄明白面试官的兴趣和工作职责。你可以使用几个在线工具，包括他们的Glassdoor Profiles，对他们进行研究）* 面试官的经验水平如何？（不同经验水平的人有不同的关注点。例如，经理可能关心你的管理能力，而团队领导可能对你的协作技能更感兴趣。如果你把眼光放在面试官更容易理解的层面上，你会很轻易给他们留下深刻印象）2）由表及里——结构要有逻辑 你的演讲应该结构合理，借此可以让你在面试陈述中保持在正确的轨道上，并防止你的面试官感到无聊。一个结构化的陈述应有一个有趣的引入，在正文中有一个令人信服的论点，以及一个值得注意的结论。虽然有趣的介绍会激发他们的兴趣，但有力的论据会让面试官相信你是这份工作的优秀候选人。一个出色的结论可以通过重申你的工作技能和经验来确保你获得这份工作的机会。对于结构化演示文稿，你可以选择创建一个项目，演示如何使用你的技能来为公司创造利益。在面试过程中，你可以使用PowerPoint等演示辅助工具来保证演示文稿的结构。每个PowerPoint幻灯片都应该是演示文稿中一个关键点的摘要。你也可以尝试将幻灯片的打印版本分发给面试小组，使你的演示即使在面试后也令人难忘。3）熟能生巧——多进行面试演练 在大多数情况下，面试陈述是增强你获得工作机会的申请阶段。因此，在进行演示时，你要避免胡言乱语或显得毫无准备。如果你想在整个面试过程中保持自信，你可能应该事先练习几次。用相机记录自己或在朋友面前进行模拟演示。通过这种方式，你可以更轻松地获得有关你的演示文稿的反馈，并在需要改进的领域开展工作。如果你决定录制你的演讲，请注意你的肢体语言。面试官通过你的语言和非语言暗示来建立对你的印象。以下是一些关于面试演讲中适当的肢体语言的提示：* 站着进行整个演示* 演讲时，保持高昂的头和直立的肩膀* 与面试官保持眼神交流（如果你站在桌子或讲台后面，那你不妨走到前面，这样他们就能清楚地看到你的表情。）* 言语要自信而权威* 在演讲间隙深呼吸无论你为面试做了多少准备，你可能仍然会对实际的面试日期感到紧张。紧张的人往往说话比平时快。然而，在演讲过程中深呼吸可以帮助你降低语速。4）稳扎稳打——遵守演示规则 在构建演示文稿时，请遵循面试官的面试规则。如果你的面试官规定所有候选人必须在八分钟内完成陈述，那就不要超过哪怕一秒钟。面试官可能会认为，任何不遵守指示的求职者都是不可靠的。因此，请始终“听话”。5）舍我其谁——做独一无二的你 就像你一样，其他求职者也会在互联网上寻找给人留下深刻印象的方法。你需要展示你的独特性，让你的面试官相信你是这个职位的理想人选。你可以通过创建一个模拟的小型项目并演示如何使用你的技能来实现所需的项目目标，从而使自己与众不同。6）心中有数——使用熟悉的技术 今天，互联网上有很多演示软件。最新演示软件的动态功能很容易分散注意力。所以，你最好跳过学习如何操作新的演示软件，而专注于在熟悉的工具上构建演示文稿。你的内容是演示文稿中最重要的部分。7）有备无患——为自己留好后路 你未来的面试官可能会提供投影仪和USB兼容设备来帮助你进行演示。不过，有备无患。有一个后备计划将确保你成功完成演示，不必担心可能出现的任何复杂情况。即使公司承诺为你的演示提供投影仪，也要带上你的笔记本电脑。你的面试官可能很少，所以即使你使用个人电脑，他们也能清楚地看到屏幕。当你的电脑出现故障时，你可以打印几份幻灯片给面试官，这也可以帮助你脱离窘境。8）投其所好——在演示文稿中使用公司品牌格式 相比其他演示文稿，面试官更有可能关注以其公司的品牌颜色设计的演示文稿。你可以在他们的网站上找到你面试官的品牌颜色和格式。如果公司在互联网上发布了演示文稿样本，你可以研究它们并使用类似的格式。9）事预则立 ——随时回答面试官很可能会有的问题 创建完演示文稿后，你需要确定面试官可能提出的任何后续问题。以下是面试官在面试陈述中询问的常见后续问题：* 你为什么推荐此解决方案？* 我们可以使用哪些资源来落实这些想法？* 我们如何说服我们的合作伙伴投资于此计划？* 你计划如何将此项目的风险降至最低？* 这个项目与我们公司的愿景有什么联系？适合初学者的简单面试演示模板 如果你在创建第一个面试演示文稿时遇到问题，我们设计了一个面试演示文稿模板来指导你。每个面试演示都应包含以下部分。1）概要。陈述你演讲的目标，突出结构，让你的面试官对你的演讲有一个大致的了解。2）关于你自己。分享你的工作经验和你拥有的任何相关技能。3）关于公司。重申公司的目标、愿景和成就。如果你必须在有限的时间内完成你的展示，请只分享与你的想法相关的目标。4）回答简报。在这个部分，你要和面试官讨论你的想法。如果你的雇主要求你在演示中回答一些问题，请在这里提供你的答案。你还应该在这里分享你的建议的优点和局限性。5）问答。你可以花一些时间让你的听众提出后续问题，并从你那里得到他们的答案。6）结论。总结你的要点，做出一个理性的结论，并向面试小组解释你的决定。7）过去成就/可交付成果。强调你以前的成功，让你的听众相信你能胜任这份工作。最佳面试演示软件下面是一些你可以用来进行专业面试演示的最好的软件：1）PowerPointPowerPoint是最常见的演示软件。任何有工作笔记本电脑的人都可以轻松访问PowerPoint。该演示软件的最新版本提供了预先设计的视觉效果，并允许用户直接在幻灯片上添加和编辑视频和音频。然而，这个软件可能会让初学者不知所措。此外，面试者可能会发现在软件上说明复杂的想法很有挑战性。2）PreziPrezi将单调的幻灯片转换为交互式演示。本演示软件是免费使用的。尽管如此，用户往往会迷失在Prezi提供的有吸引力的视觉选项中，忽视了他们的内容。此外，你不能将音频文件添加到Prezi演示文稿中。3）KeynoteKeynote演示软件仅供Mac用户使用。尽管它的美学令人印象深刻，但Keynote允许免费使用和离线访问。该软件是用户友好的。只要几个小时的练习，初学者就能做出出色的主题演讲。如果你是一个入门级的求职者，没有制作演示文稿的经验，可以考虑用这个软件开发你的演示技能。4）Google Slides谷歌幻灯片是令人印象深刻的演示软件，允许用户将动画和视频导入到他们的幻灯片中。然而，它的主题比Prezi和PowerPoint要少。与PowerPoint不同的是，这个软件对每个用户都是免费的，只要他们有一个谷歌帐户。没有Mac的初学者可以学习如何使用谷歌幻灯片构建演示文稿。在面试中做一个有说服力的陈述可以帮助你展示你的工作相关技能和个人品质，让你成为这个职位的理想候选人。根据下面的指导，学习如何做一个强有力的面试演示，给面试官留下深刻印象，从而提高你得到工作的机会。作者：Glassdoor Team 初创企业裁员减少，但生存挑战仍未解除 1月份经历了巨大的裁员浪潮后，初创企业的裁员潮在上个月有所下降，但与2022年大部分时间相比仍然处于较高水平。以下数据来自于layoffs.fyi网站。虽然该网站跟踪的是规模相对较小的初创企业，但也包括一些大型上市公司，如IBM、Salesforce和Uber在内。下面是从2022年5月到现在的统计数据：该列表包括大型公司，这就是为什么裁员似乎在1月份激增，然后在2月份再次下降的原因之一。2023年的前四周，一些美国最大的科技巨头裁员了数万名员工。亚马逊裁员了8000名员工，紧随其后的是Salesforce宣布裁员，裁员人数与亚马逊差不多。微软、谷歌、Spotify、IBM、飞利浦和SAP随后也进行了大规模的裁员。到了2月份，许多拥有最多科技员工的公司都进行了裁员。虽然一些知名品牌在上个月也进行了裁员，但相对于1月份，这些数字相对较小。例如，雅虎裁员了1600名员工，Zoom解雇了1300人。Layoffs.fyi定期更新其数据，因此2月份的总数可能会略有上升。然而，巨头科技公司是否会在2023年继续进行大规模裁员，还有待观察。但是需要注意的是，根据最新的CompTIA对美国劳工统计局数据的分析，科技行业的失业率在1月份降至1.5％；今年初许多非科技行业都经历了强劲的技术人才需求，包括保险业（1月份技术工作岗位发布数量增加了30,576个）和制造业（24,269个技术工作岗位）。尽管裁员的前景令人恐惧，但要记住，整个经济体中的企业都渴求各种类型的科技人才。作者：Glassdoor Subject: The Edition: We asked for your stories and you delivered
Body: A complimentary edition of Medium’s member-only newsletterUnlock every story on Medium, get this newsletter delivered to your inbox weekly, and directly support the writers you read most for less than $1/week when you become a member. Join Medium.Dear Medium member,We asked and you delivered. You suggested essays for our Women’s History Month list. You told us your pandemic stories. You applied to our Verified Author program.To that end, we’ve been including your work in our “Staff Picks” story list celebrating remarkable women for Women’s History Month. These pieces are essential, and eye-opening; please keep them coming. I’d also like to resurface a series that recognized one historically-overlooked group of women: Black authors. The Zora Canon was a first-of-its-kind collection of the greatest books written by African American women, assembled in collaboration with a blue-ribbon panel of authorities on women’s literature. Published three years ago, it continues to resonate with readers.Devon Price’s journey to authorship via Medium resonates as well. Price snagged a book deal after his 2018 piece, “Laziness Does Not Exist,” went viral. You can find Price’s story on Medium’s official blog, where we talked to him about his ideas. We’ll be highlighting other authors whose work has intersected with Medium over the coming months.One more: Ahead of the third anniversary of the COVID-19 epidemic, we asked Medium writers to share their pandemic stories. Nearly 600 of you responded, writing on topics ranging from the personal to the medical to the political. You can read a list of some of our favorites, or see the full range of #Pandemic Stories here (and if you’d like to share yours, just add that tag to it when you hit publish, and we’ll keep an eye out).Lastly, a note for the writers among you: We’ve just upgraded the experience of publishing to Medium on our mobile apps. To see the changes, make sure you’ve updated to the most recent version of the Medium app, and read more here.As always, thank you for reading.Scott LambVP, Content @ MediumHandpicked stories from our editorial team[Image "1*GqpC3jSG7D4dJluH0vWlHA.png"]ANNA IURCHENKODesigner at Google Health Discovering Creativity: On Your Unique Blob and the Threat of NormalcyA reflection of my journey in finding my creative self and an attempt to understand why and how creative identity can be hidden Read more[Image "1*T6ExYAwqxEgnjfN1wEHh5g.png"]GIOVANNI MALLOYData and decision scientist College Basketball’s NET Rankings, ExplainedHow data science drives March Madness Read more[Image "1*nSb8Zf0vK0qYXuYgzDAUwg.png"]SCOTT H. YOUNGAuthor of best selling book, “Ultralearning” The Biggest Issue with Long-Term ProductivityThe top researchers, programmers and entrepreneurs have more professional impact — by orders of magnitude — than their typical peers, but it’s usually not just because they’re just trying really hard Read more[Image "1*IQyG1dTlHO9ErtpCbu-ufg.png"]DANIELLE DICK, PHDDirector of the Rutgers Addiction Research Center, Professor of Psychiatry, Author of “The Child Code” What Every Parent Needs To Know About Teen Substance UseI direct the largest addiction research center in the country, and I study substance use in adolescence. Here’s what every parent needs to know about adolescent substance use. Read more[Image "1*KkPQNVRvQL1nNXLWFRjdlQ.png"]CATHERINE A. SANDERSONPoler Family Professor of Psychology at Amherst College A Simple Strategy for Boosting Happiness and Health: Spend Time in NatureWhat’s so good about spending time in nature? Here’s what empirical research reveals. Read more[Image "1*6vwB7XHCGit--oT7vyh3PQ.png"]ALEXANDRA MISLINAssociate Professor in the Department of Management at American University 5 Tips for Women to Negotiate a Higher SalaryA negotiation expert offers practical tips for getting the salary or promotion you want Read more[Image "1*W-9f8mMqryJwfR7CGJs8vw.png"]WHITNEY ALESEWriter and podcaster Angela Bassett Is Allowed to be DisappointedA reminder that Black women are allowed to feel emotions, whether you are comfortable with it or not Read more html

Subject: KurtJi, We have awesome remote U.S. jobs waiting for engineers like you.
Body:
Get an offer as early as 2 weeks.

Hi KurtJi,

I saw your profile online and wanted to reach out! You might be a great fit for many high-paying remote U.S. software engineering opportunities on Turing.com.

  • Live anywhere, enjoy rapid career growth: Live anywhere in the world, enjoy career growth opportunities formerly only available to engineers living in the Silicon Valley.

  • Full-Time, Long term opportunities: - Turing only partners with U.S companies that are hiring for full-time long term roles remotely and also work hard on re-matching you to subsequent long term opportunities.

  • Compensation: - Get paid on your terms in U.S. dollars. Tell us your pay expectations, and together we’ll agree on compensation that works for you based on your skills and experience. You get 100% of that—we charge companies to cover our costs.

  • Find jobs across levels: - Turing engages mid-level, senior-level, and tech-lead-level engineers with top U.S. companies.

  • Find jobs in 100+ Skills: - Turing has opportunities across several skills like React, Node, Python, Angular, Swift, React Native, Android, Java, Rails, Golang, PHP, Vue, DevOps, Machine Learning, and more.

START YOUR APPLICATION

Have difficulty creating your profile? Please email us at hiring@turing.com, and our team will get back to you ASAP.

Traditional recruiting is over.
Welcome to Turing.

Best Regards,
Turing Team

Body: [Image "Weekend+Read+header.png"] Read on Medium“The most important, and indeed the truly unique, contribution of management in the 20th century was the fifty-fold increase in the productivity of the manual worker in manufacturing.” — Peter DruckerIt wasn’t supposed to be like this. The “Great Boom” was supposed to last.From 1870-1970, there was an incredible 50x increase in the productivity of the average manual worker. Let me break that down so it really lands for you like it did for me:- 50x Increase: Imagine getting 50 hours of work done in one hour. Or imagine doing the work of 50 people by yourself.- On Average: We’re not just talking about a 50x increase for the most ambitious, smartest manual workers. We’re talking about all manual workers.To put the profundity in context, the “Great Boom” is one of the most amazing and under-appreciated events in economic history. The chart below captures its magnitude and uniqueness:[Image "Weekend+Read+chart.png"] To more deeply appreciate this shift, consider the following:- This is a unique event in all of history. “Modern humans first emerged about 100,000 years ago. For the next 99,800 years or so, nothing happened…Then — just a couple of hundred years ago — people started getting richer. And richer and richer still,” states Economist Steven Landsburg.- Before it happened, the average American lived on about a dollar a day (in today’s dollars). “Before 1750, almost nowhere in the world were living standards something that we would call anything but miserable and poor,” according to economic historian Joel Mokyr. Economist Steven Landsburg adds, “Almost everyone lived on the modern equivalent of $400 to $600 a year, just above the subsistence level.”- Before it happened, day-to-day life was brutal. “In 1870, farm and urban working-class family members [in the United States] bathed in a large tub in the kitchen, often the only heated room in the home, after carrying cold water in pails from the outside and warming it over the open-hearth fireplace,” according to economic historian Robert Gordon.Bottom line: The people alive between 1870–1970 experienced unprecedented change. Now, imagine being an adult in 1970. Think about how you’d see the world…Unlock the full story — plus millions more — when you become a Medium member for less than $1/week.Join Medium html

Body: 最近，科技行业的工作岗位消失的速度似乎比一锅滚水里的蒸汽还快。春节餐饮美食餐馆餐厅上新促销营销简约复古(2) )数据科学求职训练营 )10大领域16大实战项目刷到手软 )NLP、Fintech、推荐系统经验值蹭蹭蹭涨 )联系底部微信号咨询课程Syllabus！ )pexels-arun-prasanth-gopalsamy-15708316 )本周公开课：如何使用ChatGPT分析数据科学问题 )ChatGPT ) 也可以做很多很酷的事情，其中一个是写代码。它可以帮助你使用自然语言创建SQL查询 ) ，解决你的编码问题，将你的Python代码 ) 转换为R, Java, Julia等！那么如何使用ChatGPT分析数据科学 ) 问题？3月18日 周六 5:00-6:00 PM PT )点击免费报名，一起来学习吧！ )pexels-cottonbro-studio-4065895 )科技巨头大规模裁员 )但情况可能并没有你想的那么糟糕 )根据Layoffs.fyi网站（该网站一直在跟进科技公司的裁员情况）汇编的数据，自今年年初以来，297家科技公司 ) 解雇了近9.5万名员工。如果这一势头持续下去，该行业可能会在2023年裁员90多万人。根据该网站的数据，这几乎是2022年该行业总数 ) 的六倍。但科技行业 ) 的天并没有完全塌下来，至少目前还没有...点击开始阅读 )pexels-nataliya-vaitkevich-8062365 )高级SQL技巧与窍门： )数据分析师必备！ )基础SQL ) 非常简单，但是把SQL ) 用得正确而高级并不是那么容易。下面是一些更高级的SQL技巧 ) ，它们将帮助你执行更复杂的查询，或者只是更好地执行基础查询。公用表表达式 ) （CTE）：CTE ) 允许你通过创建可在单个查询中多次重用的中间结果，将复杂的查询分解为更小、更易于管理的部分。点击开始阅读 )数据应用学院订阅福利来啦！分享下方海报到朋友圈，添加微信小助手(dataapplab_wechat)，领取我们独家整理的SQL Cheat Sheet！Data Application Lab, 6131 Orangethorpe Ave, STE 170B, Buena Park, CA 90620Manage preferences )LinkedIn )YouTube )Website ) html

Body: Top stories for Kurt-----Question: Is the University of Wisconsin (Madison) better than the University of Michigan?Answer from Lori SkedelskyI did my undergraduate degree at UW and my graduate degree at UM. My findings are they are both beautiful campuses. I learned more in Wisconsin. Michigan is great too. ButRead More: -----Question: If I have a 3.6 GPA and a 1540 SAT (760 ERW 780 Math), would a school like Stanford consider me academically qualified?Answer from Joshua GrossKim is correct; the issue is not whether they would consider you academically qualified (they almost certainly would), but whether you would be competitive for admission.Read More: -----Question: Is San Francisco the worst place in America? My very short time there almost scarred me for life. I am desperately sorry for the homeless there but it is a filthy hell hole and I can't believe a place could be worse.Answer from Tēnn Khong Lîm (Ah Lîm)Absolutely not. I’ve been to several cities much worse than San Francisco. If San Francisco scarred you for life, don’t ever think about going to:* Detroit* Flint*Read More: -----Question: Why did you stop being a data scientist?Answer from Naitik ChandakWhy did I stop being a Data Scientist.? Furious the snake returned and bit the sRead More: -----Question: Should I go to USC or ASU?Answer from BrianAs an alumnus of both ASU and USC, I am heavily leaning towards USC. Day 527Asked in Let us walk together, Answer from Victoria NgA son who is in the middle of selling something who carried his dying mother with him. He isn’t going to leave her home alone, but he brings her out everywhere he goes. ThRead More: -----Question: Why does a second PhD not sound good to some people, despite my ability to do so?Answer from Colin RiegelsGetting a second PhD is usually about as much use as passing your driving test for a second time.The real purpose of a PhD is to establish that you can conduct advancedRead More: -----Question: Why does China call itself "中国" (i.e. "central/middle kingdom")? Other countries' names are translated to Chinese according to the pronunciation.Answer from Leo WangGermany is 德国, which means "moral country" by the characters;America is 美国, which means "beautiful country" by the characters;Britain is 英国, which means "outstanding cRead More: -----Question: Why does Britain always seem to win every war they get involved in?Answer from Alastair MellorThis anecdote was told to me by a colleague who was a pilot in the British Army.
